This is my configuration for linux fedora based on my own experience and various tutorials.


RPM Fusion repository: https://rpmfusion.org/Configuration
sudo dnf install https://mirrors.rpmfusion.org/free/fedora/rpmfusion-free-release-$(rpm -E %fedora).noarch.rpm https://mirrors.rpmfusion.org/nonfree/fedora/rpmfusion-nonfree-release-$(rpm -E %fedora).noarch.rpm


AppStream metadata
sudo dnf groupupdate core


Multimedia and codecs
sudo dnf groupupdate sound-and-video
sudo dnf install -y libdvdcss
sudo dnf install -y gstreamer1-plugins-{bad-\*,good-\*,ugly-\*,base} gstreamer1-libav --exclude=gstreamer1-plugins-bad-free-devel ffmpeg gstreamer-ffmpeg 
sudo dnf install -y lame\* --exclude=lame-devel
sudo dnf group upgrade --with-optional Multimedia
sudo dnf install ffmpeg vlc


Tainted repos
sudo dnf install rpmfusion-free-release-tainted
sudo dnf install dnf-plugins-core


Flatpak setup: https://flatpak.org/setup/Fedora/
sudo flatpak remote-add --if-not-exists flathub https://flathub.org/repo/flathub.flatpakrepo
flatpak update


Install VAAPI - Intel GPU
lspci | grep VGA
sudo dnf install libva libva-intel-driver libva-vdpau-driver libva-utils libva-intel-hybrid-driver


Thermald (Intel Thermal Daemon): https://github.com/intel/thermal_daemon 
sudo dnf groupinstall "Development Tools" "C Development Tools and Libraries"
sudo yum install automake gcc gcc-c++ glib-devel libxml2-devel dbus-glib-devel autoconf-archive gtk-doc upower-devel xz-devel libevdev-devel

Download latest release: https://github.com/intel/thermal_daemon/tags
./autogen.sh prefix=/
make
sudo make install

1. Start service: sudo systemctl start thermald.service
2. Get Status: sudo systemctl status thermald.service
3. Stop service: sudo systemctl stop thermald.service
4. Terminate using DBUS I/F: sudo test/test_pref.sh  (and select "TERMINATE" choice)
5. Enable Service: sudo systemctl enable thermald
6. Start service: sudo systemctl start thermald.service


Power profiles daemon: https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/hadess/power-profiles-daemon
sudo dnf install power-profiles-daemon

Powertop: https://01.org/powertop/overview
sudo dnf install powertop


GRUB Setup:
GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX="rhgb quiet acpi_osi=Linux pcie_aspm=force drm.vblankoffdelay=1 zswap.enabled=1 zswap.compressor=lz4 i915.enable_guc=2 scsi_mod.use_blk_mq=1 intel_iommu=on intel_pstate=passive mitigations=off"

sudo grub2-mkconfig -o /boot/efi/EFI/fedora/grub.cfg


TRIM Support
sudo systemctl enable fstrim.timer
sudo systemctl start fstrim.timer
sudo fstrim -v /


DNF Flags:
echo 'fastestmirror=1' | sudo tee -a /etc/dnf/dnf.conf
echo 'max_parallel_downloads=10' | sudo tee -a /etc/dnf/dnf.conf
echo 'deltarpm=true' | sudo tee -a /etc/dnf/dnf.conf
cat /etc/dnf/dnf.conf


Set Hostname
hostnamectl set-hostname fedora


Check Locales
localectl status
timedatectl


Install updates and reboot
sudo dnf upgrade --refresh
sudo dnf check
sudo dnf autoremove
sudo fwupdmgr get-devices
sudo fwupdmgr refresh --force
sudo fwupdmgr get-updates
sudo fwupdmgr update
sudo reboot now


Fish - A Friendly Interactive Shell: https://fedoramagazine.org/fish-a-friendly-interactive-shell/
sudo dnf install -y fish util-linux-user
chsh -s /usr/bin/fish

Add the ~/.local/bin to my $PATH persistently in Fish
mkdir -p /home/$USER/.local/bin
set -Ua fish_user_paths /home/$USER/.local/bin
bash -c 'echo $PATH'


Gnome Extensions and Tweaks
sudo dnf install gnome-extensions-app gnome-tweaks
sudo dnf install gnome-shell-extension-appindicator
https://extensions.gnome.org/extension/906/sound-output-device-chooser/


Snap support
sudo dnf install snapd
sudo ln -s /var/lib/snapd/snap /snap
sudo reboot now
sudo snap refresh


Google Chrome: https://www.google.com/linuxrepositories/
wget https://dl.google.com/linux/linux_signing_key.pub
sudo rpm --import linux_signing_key.pub
rpm -qi gpg-pubkey-7fac5991-*


Chromium-freeworld - VAAPI Support: https://major.io/2019/10/20/install-chromium-with-vaapi-on-fedora-30/
sudo dnf -y install chromium-freeworld
Enable DRM:
sudo cp /opt/google/chrome/libwidevinecdm.so /usr/lib64/chromium-freeworld/


Steam:
sudo dnf install steam libtxc_dxtn.i686 ibtxc_dxtn.x86_64


POP OS Theme

Install Pop-Shell Tiling Extension:
sudo dnf install gnome-shell-extension-pop-shell


Pop shell keyboard shortcuts:
sudo dnf install -y make cargo rust gtk3-devel
git clone https://github.com/pop-os/shell-shortcuts /home/$USER/fedora/pop-theme/shell-shortcuts
cd /home/$USER/fedora/pop-theme/shell-shortcuts
make
sudo make install
pop-shell-shortcuts


Pop GTK theme:
sudo dnf install -y sassc meson glib2-devel
git clone https://github.com/pop-os/gtk-theme /home/$USER/fedora/pop-theme/gtk-theme
cd /home/$USER/fedora/pop-theme/gtk-theme
meson build && cd build
ninja
sudo ninja install
gsettings set org.gnome.desktop.interface gtk-theme "Pop"


Pop icon theme:
git clone https://github.com/pop-os/icon-theme /home/$USER/fedora/pop-theme/icon-theme
cd /home/$USER/fedora/pop-theme/icon-theme
meson build
sudo ninja -C "build" install
gsettings set org.gnome.desktop.interface icon-theme "Pop"
gsettings set org.gnome.desktop.interface cursor-theme "Pop"


Pop fonts:
sudo dnf install -y fira-code-fonts 'mozilla-fira*' 'google-roboto*'
Go into Gnome Tweaks and make the following changes in Fonts:
1. Interface Text: Fira Sans Book 10
2. Document Text: Roboto Slab Regular 11
3. Monospace Text: Fira Mono Regular 11
4. Legacy Window Titles: Fira Sans SemiBold 10
5. Hinting: Slight
6. Antialiasing: Standard (greyscale)
7. Scaling Factor: 1.00


Pop Gnome Terminal Theme:

Text
        Custom font: Fira Mono 12
        Deactivate Terminal bell
Colors
        Deactivate Use colors from system theme
        Built-in schemes: Custom
        Default color: Text #F2F2F2 | Background: #333333
        Bold color (unchecked) #73C48F
        Cursor color (checked): Text #49B9C7 | Background: #F6F6F6
        Highlight color (checked): Text #FFFFFF | Background: #48B9C7
        Uncheck Transparend background
Palette colors:
        0: #333333 1: #CC0000 2: #4E9A06 3: #C4A000 4: #3465A4 5: #75507B 6: #06989A 7: #D3D7CF
        8: #88807C 9: #F15D22 10: #73C48F 11: #FFCE51 12: #48B9C7 13: #AD7FA8 14: #34E2E2 15: #EEEEEC
        Uncheck Show bold text in bright colors
	Right click on the Pop profile and set as default.

Setup .bashrc (the file is in my repository)


Apps:
Firefox 

Extensions
    Bitwarden
    Disable HTML5 Autoplay
    GNOME Shell-Integration
    HTTPS Everywhere
    uBlock Origin
    H264IFY
    
Plugins
    OpenH264-Videocodec
    Widevine Content Decryption Module

Theme: 
git clone https://github.com/rafaelmardojai/firefox-gnome-theme/ /home/$USER/fedora/firefox-gnome-theme
cd /home/$USER/fedora/firefox-gnome-theme
./scripts/install.sh



Microsoft Fonts
sudo dnf install -y curl cabextract xorg-x11-font-utils fontconfigsudo rpm -i https://downloads.sourceforge.net/project/mscorefonts2/rpms/msttcore-fonts-installer-2.6-1.noarch.rpm


Skype
flatpak install -y skype


Zoom
flatpak install -y zoom


OpenH264 in Firefox
sudo dnf config-manager --set-enabled fedora-cisco-openh264
sudo dnf install -y gstreamer1-plugin-openh264 mozilla-openh264


OBS
sudo snap install obs-studio --edge
sudo snap connect obs-studio:audio-record
sudo snap connect obs-studio:avahi-control
sudo snap connect obs-studio:camera
sudo snap connect obs-studio:jack1
sudo snap connect obs-studio:joystick
sudo snap connect obs-studio:removable-media
